        "69085": {
          "vnum": 69085,
          "name": "Beneath the Ingeen Tree",
          "description": "Cool shade lends comfort as you wander beneath the massive oak known as the Ingeen Tree. Considered sacred, the Ingeen Tree is the destination of pilgrimage for hobbits from all of Ishar. A seemingly endless flight of wooden steps spirals up the trunk into a homey chapel set in the tree`s branches. To the south lies a modest house with a blackened lead front door. A pleasant clearing in the center of the village lies to the east.",
